Barrick halts Peru project , takes charge . Barrick Gold Corp said on Tuesday it will not proceed with the Cerro Corona project in Peru and as a result will take a C $ 38 million after - tax charge to third quarter earnings . Barrick said while its gold and copper mineralization is substantial , further exploration has found the extent of the find was not sufficient to meet Barrick ' s criteria for development . Barrick said it has decided to channel its development capital into its recently acquired Arequipa assets and other " promising " exploration properties . " They have the potential to make much more significant additions to reserves and production , " Barrick executive vice president Alan Hill said in a statement . - - Reuters Toronto bureau 416 - 941 - 8100 
